  "local_port": 57576,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some recipes using 4 ounces of steak?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are a few recipe ideas using 4 ounces of steak:\n\n1. **Steak Tacos**:\n   - **Ingredients**: 4 oz steak, small tortillas, diced onions, chopped cilantro, lime wedges, salsa, salt, and pepper.\n   - **Instructions**: Season the steak with salt and pepper. Cook on a hot skillet until desired doneness. Let it rest, then slice thinly. Serve in warmed tortillas with onions, cilantro, salsa, and a squeeze of lime.\n\n2. **Steak and Vegetable Stir-fry**:\n   - **Ingredients**: 4 oz steak, a mix of vegetables (like bell peppers, broccoli, and carrots), soy sauce, garlic, ginger, and sesame oil.\n   - **Instructions**: Slice steak thinly. Stir-fry in a hot pan with sesame oil, garlic, and ginger. Add vegetables, stir-fry until tender, then add soy sauce. Serve hot over rice or noodles.\n\n3. **Steak Salad**:\n   - **Ingredients**: 4 oz steak, mixed salad greens, cherry tomatoes, red onion, cucumber, vinaigrette, salt, and pepper.\n   - **Instructions**: Season and grill or pan-sear the steak. Let it rest, then slice. Arrange greens on a plate, top with steak slices, tomatoes, onions, and cucumber. Drizzle with vinaigrette.\n\n4. **Philly Cheesesteak Sandwich**:\n   - **Ingredients**: 4 oz steak, a hoagie roll, provolone cheese, saut\u00e9ed onions, and bell peppers.\n   - **Instructions**: Thinly slice the steak and cook with onions and peppers. Transfer to a hoagie roll, top with cheese. Melt the cheese under a broiler or in a pan. Serve hot.\n\n5. **Steak and Egg Breakfast**:\n   - **Ingredients**: 4 oz steak, eggs, salt, pepper, and butter.\n   - **Instructions**: Season and cook the steak in butter until your desired doneness. Let it rest. Fry eggs to your liking. Serve steak slices with eggs on the side.\n\nThese recipes highlight the versatility of a small amount of steak, making delicious meals with ample flavor. Adjust seasoning and additional ingredients to taste.",
